  "text": "Kubernetes RBAC verb coverage audit completed. The analysis identifies all Go source files that define and enforce allowed RBAC verbs (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete, deletecollection).\n\n## Key Findings:\n\n### Verb Definition Files:\n\n1. **Bootstrap Policy Definitions** (kubernetes--v1.32.0/plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/policy.go):\n   - Defines verb groupings: Write = [\"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\"]\n   - ReadWrite = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\"]\n   - Read = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n   - ReadUpdate = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n   - Also defines special verbs: \"escalate\", \"impersonate\", \"bind\"\n\n2. **Constant Definitions** (pkg/apis/rbac/types.go and staging versions):\n   - VerbAll constant set to \"*\" represents permission for all verbs\n   - Defined consistently across v1, v1alpha1, and v1beta1 API versions\n   - Located in both kubernetes--v1.32.0 and api--v0.32.0\n\n### Verb Enforcement and Validation:\n\n1. **Authorization Enforcement** (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go):\n   - RuleAllows(): Checks if a request's verb matches policy rules using VerbMatches() helper\n   - RulesAllow(): Checks if any rule allows the request\n   - Integrates with ResourceMatches(), APIGroupMatches(), and ResourceNameMatches() for complete authorization\n\n2. **Verb Matching Functions** (pkg/apis/rbac/v1/evaluation_helpers.go):\n   - VerbMatches(): Verifies if a policy rule's verbs include the requested verb or VerbAll (\"*\")\n   - APIGroupMatches(): Checks API group authorization\n   - ResourceMatches(): Checks resource authorization with subresource support\n   - ResourceNameMatches(): Checks specific resource instance authorization\n   - NonResourceURLMatches(): Checks non-resource URL authorization\n\n3. **Rule Building and Validation** (pkg/apis/rbac/helpers.go):\n   - PolicyRuleBuilder with Rule() method validates:\n     - Verbs are required for all rules\n     - Non-resource rules cannot have apiGroups, resources, or resourceNames\n     - Resource rules must have apiGroups\n     - Resource names cannot be used with verbs: list, watch, create, deletecollection\n   - NewRule() creates PolicyRuleBuilder instances\n\n4. **Escalation Prevention** (pkg/registry/rbac/escalation_check.go):\n   - EscalationAllowed(): Checks if user is in system:masters group\n   - RoleEscalationAuthorized(): Verifies escalate verb authorization on clusterroles/roles\n   - BindingAuthorized(): Verifies bind verb authorization for role binding creation\n\n5. **Policy Comparison and Coverage** (staging/src/k8s.io/component-helpers/auth/rbac/validation/policy_comparator.go):\n   - Covers(): Determines if ownerRules cover servantRules for escalation checks\n   - BreakdownRule(): Breaks down complex rules into atomic verb+resource+name combinations\n   - ruleCovers(): Checks if individual rules cover sub-rules using verb matching with VerbAll wildcard\n\n6. **Rule Resolution and Validation** (pkg/registry/rbac/validation/rule.go):\n   - ConfirmNoEscalation(): Validates that users don't escalate privileges beyond their own permissions\n   - Uses Covers() to validate rule coverage\n   - Part of RoleBinding and ClusterRoleBinding validation\n\n### Integration Chain:\n\nThe verb enforcement follows this chain:\n1. Request reaches authorization filter with HTTP method/Kubernetes verb\n2. RBACAuthorizer.Authorize() invokes RuleAllows() for each applicable rule\n3. RuleAllows() calls VerbMatches() to check if rule permits the verb\n4. VerbMatches() checks against rule.Verbs slice, supporting VerbAll wildcard\n5. If verb matches, ResourceMatches() and other criteria are checked\n6. For role modifications, ConfirmNoEscalation() validates permissions using Covers()\n7. Covers() breaks down rules and uses verb matching to ensure users don't exceed their authority\n\n### API Type Definitions:\n\nThe PolicyRule struct (defined in api--v0.32.0 and staging/src/k8s.io/api/rbac/) has Verbs field:\n- Type: []string\n- Represents all Kubernetes verbs or custom verbs\n- Supports \"*\" (VerbAll) for permission on all verbs\n- Defined in v1 (stable), v1beta1 (beta), and v1alpha1 (alpha) versions\n\n### Special Verbs Identified:\n\nBeyond the standard CRUD verbs, the codebase also defines and enforces special verbs:\n- \"escalate\": Grants ability to create/update roles with elevated permissions\n- \"impersonate\": Grants ability to act as another user/service account\n- \"bind\": Grants ability to create role bindings\n- All enforced through the same verb matching mechanism\n\nThe audit confirms that Kubernetes RBAC provides complete verb coverage with consistent enforcement across all authorization decision points."
